Description: This Vantage LP style electric guitar in trans mocha brown finish and set neck was likely made in Japan during the late 1980s. It is constructed of mahogany, both the body and the neck, and is heavy and very solidly built. It is in good working and good but not perfect cosmetic condition. The guitar has been played but the frets have a lot of life left, and the neck is straight. The tuners (that appear to be replacements) and electronics all work as they should. The finish has a lot of minor bumps and bruises with a couple of notable gouges that are featured in photos. A previous owner dabbed white paint dots on the top as markers for the volume and tone knobs; they look fine but are obviously hand done. The finish on the hardware is in good condition with some tarnishing and signs of wear. I didn’t check but I suspect that the pickups and controls are made in Korea as well. There is a “sharpie” autograph on the left bout that was represented by the seller as being by Sammy Hagar, but I have no proof of this. The signature is very hard to see and easy to miss.
